that everything's okay,

12:28.081 --> 12:30.148
So that you can feel
like everything's okay,

12:30.217 --> 12:32.917
And it-it it's not!
All right? It's not okay.

12:32.919 --> 12:35.120
For-for me, or for crystal.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.455
And you have to deal with that.

12:37.590 --> 12:39.657
(papers rustle,
computer clunks)

12:39.726 --> 12:42.193
You deal with you.

12:42.195 --> 12:44.595
(footsteps recede,
beads jingle)

12:47.501 --> 12:49.133
<i> Bea: I don't believe ya,</i>
<i> melvin.</i>

12:49.136 --> 12:51.068
If ya love the kraken still,

12:51.104 --> 12:52.736
Why don't ya join it

12:52.773 --> 12:55.006
At the bottom of the cold,
dark sea?

12:55.008 --> 12:57.075
- I was a fool.

12:58.612 --> 13:01.145
A fool.

13:01.148 --> 13:02.880
Blinded by the ocean's
mistress.

13:04.350 --> 13:06.250
But a fool I am, no more.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.421
Doris, my darling,

13:10.423 --> 13:12.023
My love burns for you,

13:12.092 --> 13:13.591
