- I need you to stop acting

13:26.506 --> 13:28.739
And start being.

13:28.775 --> 13:30.942
What is going on in there?

13:31.077 --> 13:33.110
How are you accessing
real emotions

13:33.146 --> 13:35.446
Through imaginary
circumstances?

13:36.650 --> 13:39.583
- Um, dave, we're talkin'
about an evil squid, here.

13:39.619 --> 13:42.253
- Haven't you ever experienced
an epic love?

13:42.289 --> 13:44.856
Something all-consuming
and deep?

13:44.991 --> 13:47.458
That's what we need here!

13:47.494 --> 13:50.661
I need to feel your passion
for this woman.

13:50.730 --> 13:54.265
- I've been head over heels
for bea since we were kids.

13:54.301 --> 13:56.801
- Not buying it.
Not your fault...

13:56.870 --> 14:00.338
But to share publicly,
your private life,

14:00.407 --> 14:03.408
Requires a fearlessness.

14:03.543 --> 14:06.010
That's why we actors
are so highly paid.

14:06.046 --> 14:08.312
That's why we are adored
by all.

14:10.150 --> 14:12.049
Move.

14:12.085 --> 14:15.152
Take it from uh,
love the kraken.

14:15.188 --> 14:17.221
(bea clears her throat)
(lights clunk on)

14:17.257 --> 14:19.324
- I don't believe you, melvin.

14:19.326 --> 14:22.226
If you love the kraken still,
why don't ya join it

14:22.229 --> 14:25.162
At the bottom of the cold,
dark, sea?

14:25.198 --> 14:27.065
- I was a fool!

14:27.200 --> 14:30.501
A fool blinded by
the ocean's mistress.

14:30.570 --> 14:32.503
But a fool I am no more!

14:32.572 --> 14:34.372
Doris, my darling.

14:34.374 --> 14:35.807
- Oh!

14:35.942 --> 14:37.741
- My love... Burns for you.

14:38.778 --> 14:40.378
Like syphilis.

14:40.380 --> 14:42.447
I have solved the meaning
of life!

14:42.582 --> 14:44.048
- (chuckles lovingly)
- 'tis you! 'tis me!

14:44.117 --> 14:47.217
Sailing the high seas!
Finding the kraken's child.

14:47.254 --> 14:49.120
Ripping out its innards
together.

14:49.189 --> 14:51.555
And making sweet love
in its viscera,

14:51.625 --> 14:54.192
Right there on the deck.
- Oh, melvin.

14:54.327 --> 14:56.260
How I've longed to hear
you say--

14:56.296 --> 14:58.129
- (shocked gasps)
bea: (mumbles)

14:58.131 --> 15:01.065
<i> Men: Uh oh.</i>
<i> (laughs)</i>

15:01.067 --> 15:03.000
<i> - Get 'er!</i>

15:03.069 --> 15:05.737
♪♪♪

15:05.739 --> 15:07.504
(bea gasps for air)

15:08.608 --> 15:11.542
- That... Is how you stay
in the moment.

15:11.544 --> 15:13.211
Let's run it again.
And again.

15:13.346 --> 15:15.947
Until we feel it in our bones.

15:15.949 --> 15:18.582
- It's in someone's bone.
- (chuckling)

15:21.621 --> 15:24.021
- Find yourself another melvin.

15:24.090 --> 15:28.159
♪♪♪

15:28.228 --> 15:29.827
- (sighs)

15:29.829 --> 15:31.963
(loud drumming,
incoherent singing)

15:31.965 --> 15:34.098
<i> - (guests giggle)</i>
<i> - yeah.</i>

15:34.100 --> 15:37.134
(drumming and singing
continues)

15:38.838 --> 15:40.304
- Whoa! Whoa!

15:40.307 --> 15:42.039
What do you think
that you're doing?

15:42.108 --> 15:44.242
- I'm manifesting meaningful
change.

15:44.244 --> 15:47.444
- No, you're manifesting a
drunk and disorderly charge.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.180
- I hurt sammy.

15:49.182 --> 15:51.749
Crystal.
Everyone.

15:51.884 --> 15:54.686
I have always been hovering
close to rock bottom, sis.

15:54.821 --> 15:56.921
I can see it,
but I've never quite hit it.

15:56.923 --> 15:59.723
And I need to hit it before
meaningful change can happen!

15:59.759 --> 16:01.392
<i> (girl giggles)</i>

16:01.428 --> 16:03.227
- This is my plunge.

16:03.263 --> 16:04.928
(drumming and singing resume)

16:04.965 --> 16:07.465
- You're like a naked babe
in the woods.

16:07.534 --> 16:09.066
♪ oh

16:09.135 --> 16:10.802
♪ oh

16:10.804 --> 16:13.404
- In desperate need of a wolf
mother to rear you.

16:13.539 --> 16:15.273
♪ oh, oh, oh

16:15.408 --> 16:17.741
- This is a desperate cry
for help!

16:17.777 --> 16:20.644
- No! This is a naked
drum solo for help!

16:21.715 --> 16:22.980
♪ oh!

16:22.983 --> 16:24.648
(drumming)

16:24.684 --> 16:26.818
- I hear your cry, brother!

16:26.820 --> 16:28.952
- You do?
- Yes.

16:30.523 --> 16:32.356
And... Oh, my god.

16:32.392 --> 16:35.459
And I am going to help you.

16:35.528 --> 16:37.261
How? I don't know,

16:37.263 --> 16:39.497
But it's going to be kind,

16:39.566 --> 16:41.832
And nurturing, and...

16:41.901 --> 16:43.501
(children giggling)

16:43.570 --> 16:45.503
- Avert your eyes, assholes!

16:45.505 --> 16:49.907
♪♪♪

16:49.909 --> 16:52.876
I'm gonna nurture the shit
out of you.

16:55.849 --> 16:57.848
Nora: I gotta give the
switchboards a rest.

16:57.884 --> 16:59.584
Who knew foxton was such
a breeding ground

16:59.586 --> 17:01.786
For true crime enthusiasts?

17:01.921 --> 17:04.355
Anyway, speaking of heinous
crimes,

17:04.357 --> 17:07.525
Here is a randomly selected
b-side.

17:07.527 --> 17:09.594
(buttons click)

17:09.729 --> 17:11.896
(music starts)
(cell phone buzzes)

17:14.534 --> 17:16.667
(thumb taps)
hello?

17:16.669 --> 17:18.469
<i> Andres: Is this nora</i>
<i> finley-cullen?</i>

17:18.505 --> 17:20.804
- Yes.
- So great to connect.

17:20.840 --> 17:22.873
<i> This is andres</i>
<i> from soundmaus la.</i>

17:22.909 --> 17:24.475
- Sound what?

17:24.511 --> 17:26.277
<i> - Listen, we're massive fans</i>
<i> of "milk crate confessionals".</i>

17:26.412 --> 17:28.412
<i> We'd love to bring you down</i>
<i> to la and talk partnership.</i>

17:28.415 --> 17:30.381
We just need--
- my banking info?

17:30.383 --> 17:32.216
Nice try, jerko.
(taps call off, phone thuds)

17:32.218 --> 17:33.917
(scoffs)

17:35.288 --> 17:37.020
- Okay, we need the manifest

17:37.057 --> 17:38.756
To find out which truck
we want when it passes by.

17:38.758 --> 17:40.424
- Oh, I've seen my fair share
of mafia movies,

17:40.427 --> 17:42.226
So I'm well versed.

17:42.228 --> 17:44.928
This is the part where we
convince the dispatcher, right?

17:44.964 --> 17:46.163
(gun clicks)
(gasps) god, that's not real,

17:46.299 --> 17:48.132
Is it? Is that real?
- Yeah, it's a replica.

17:48.134 --> 17:50.067
The bullets are real.
- Okay, no, no.

17:50.070 --> 17:51.335
No one said anything
about violence.

17:51.471 --> 17:53.704
- Nothin' to say.
If they play nice.

17:53.840 --> 17:56.073
- Wait, hold on.
Uh, uh...

17:57.910 --> 17:59.710
What if I go in?
- (annoyed sigh)

17:59.846 --> 18:01.479
- Come on, if things go south,

18:01.614 --> 18:03.548
Who's gonna sell, "this isn't
the ladies room," better?

18:03.550 --> 18:06.083
Him or me?
- She's got a point.

18:06.119 --> 18:08.619
♪♪♪

18:08.754 --> 18:10.921
(foliage rustles under foot)

18:13.426 --> 18:15.059
<i> Rhian: The most effective</i>
<i> response to any problem...</i>

18:15.128 --> 18:16.727
<i> Is prevention.</i>

18:16.729 --> 18:18.762
But since you're already
born and raised,

18:18.798 --> 18:22.600
The most caring and nurturing
thing that I can do for you

18:22.669 --> 18:25.403
Is give you an intervention.

18:25.538 --> 18:27.738
- We've tried that.
So many times!

18:27.807 --> 18:29.540
I'm uninterventionable.

18:29.609 --> 18:32.143
- But that's because you needed
the support of all of us,

18:32.145 --> 18:34.411
But attendance was paltry
'cause it wasn't mandatory.

18:34.447 --> 18:36.514
It will be different this time.

18:36.649 --> 18:40.417
Family rituals can serve
as powerful leverage points

18:40.419 --> 18:42.620
To support healthy
behaviour change.

18:42.689 --> 18:44.288
And serve as unique

18:44.357 --> 18:46.824
Intervention delivery
strategies.

18:46.959 --> 18:49.159
Family rituals, ry.

18:49.195 --> 18:50.961
Fa-mi-ly!

18:51.030 --> 18:54.365
This family is going to sit
down and have dinner together.

18:54.367 --> 18:57.768
We are going to have
a ritual dinnervention.

18:57.770 --> 18:59.437
And we're gonna, you know,

18:59.439 --> 19:00.971
Talk about our feelings,

19:01.007 --> 19:03.607
And everyone will be there,
or I will kill them...

19:03.676 --> 19:06.077
With my kindness

19:06.212 --> 19:07.611
And carbohydrates.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.847
- We'll all be there.

19:09.982 --> 19:12.649
I can show sammy and crystal
that I put family first.

19:12.685 --> 19:15.653
I can be responsible.
And change.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.555
- Yes.
- And then they can forgive me.

19:17.624 --> 19:20.457
- And I can show everyone
that I'm not just selfless.

19:20.527 --> 19:24.295
I am the empress
of selflessness.

19:24.430 --> 19:25.963
- All hail us!

19:26.032 --> 19:27.931
Let's get cookin', sis!

19:27.967 --> 19:30.300
Let the dinnervention begin.

19:33.206 --> 19:35.339
<i> Terry: It's a fairly quiet</i>
<i> town.</i>

19:35.341 --> 19:37.474
Few summer drunks, lost dogs.
- Dogs.

19:37.510 --> 19:39.410
- The odd domestic.

19:39.412 --> 19:41.345
Then of course, my in-laws.

19:41.347 --> 19:43.681
- Uh, our in-laws, amirite?

19:43.750 --> 19:45.683
- Yeah. Uh, speaking of which,

19:45.685 --> 19:48.352
I need to respond to an
indecent exposure report...

19:50.023 --> 19:51.488
At the moonshine.

19:51.624 --> 19:53.624
- Well, wait, what about me?
- What about you?

19:53.759 --> 19:55.492
- Oh, I thought my first day
on the shadowing job

19:55.528 --> 19:57.494
Would be a bit more,
you know, pizzazz!

19:59.566 --> 20:01.098
- You were an accountant cop,
right?

20:01.233 --> 20:02.333
- Undercover accountant cop.
- Right.

20:02.468 --> 20:04.067
- Maybe you've got something
like that?

20:04.103 --> 20:06.103
You know, deep cover
for a veteran operative.

20:06.239 --> 20:07.905
- Yeah... Answering phones.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.540
Taking messages.

20:09.609 --> 20:11.575
Watering the ficus.

20:11.611 --> 20:13.911
You handle that, and I may...

20:14.046 --> 20:16.514
Have you reconcile
the petty cash receipts.

20:16.649 --> 20:18.649
- (sighs, defeated)
- nah!

20:21.387 --> 20:23.887
That's you.

20:23.957 --> 20:26.189
(footsteps recede)

20:26.226 --> 20:28.459
- And if... If I need
keys to the armoury?

20:30.230 --> 20:31.395
(door slides shut)

20:32.865 --> 20:34.665
(insects buzz, birds chirp)

20:34.701 --> 20:37.134
(door creaks)

20:37.203 --> 20:39.003
(shuts lightly)

20:44.944 --> 20:46.376
<i> (distant chatter)</i>

20:48.447 --> 20:50.014
(paper rustles)

20:50.083 --> 20:52.483
(chair rattles)

20:52.485 --> 20:55.352
(footsteps recede)

20:55.354 --> 20:57.087
(door opens and closes)

20:58.324 --> 21:00.224
(quick, light footsteps)

21:02.295 --> 21:04.027
(papers rustle)

21:05.765 --> 21:07.498
(toilet flushes)

21:09.535 --> 21:11.368
- Oh, my god! The manifest!

21:11.437 --> 21:13.237
(door closes)

21:13.239 --> 21:17.908
♪♪♪

21:18.044 --> 21:19.743
(locust chirps)

21:21.113 --> 21:22.713
- Shoo! Shoo!

21:22.749 --> 21:26.917
♪♪♪

21:26.986 --> 21:28.986
- Ah!
(locust chirping)

21:29.121 --> 21:30.721
(pants ruffle)

21:33.459 --> 21:35.192
- Huh.

21:37.463 --> 21:40.097
(grunting, belt jingles)

21:40.166 --> 21:42.099
(grunting)

21:45.738 --> 21:48.171
(camera clicks)

21:48.207 --> 21:50.941
(door clicks open)
(relieved sigh)

21:50.977 --> 21:53.010
(gasps) okay, it's okay.
I got it.

21:53.012 --> 21:57.614
♪♪♪

21:57.650 --> 21:59.616
- Second thoughts?
- No.

21:59.686 --> 22:02.119
If you're gonna use me,
use me.

22:02.188 --> 22:04.154
We do this my way.
No violence.

22:05.491 --> 22:07.958
- Your way's been working.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.893
So far.

22:09.962 --> 22:13.364
♪♪♪

22:13.366 --> 22:14.831
Oh!

22:18.104 --> 22:24.107
♪♪♪

22:24.143 --> 22:26.243
♪♪♪

22:26.245 --> 22:29.980
♪ green sweater
the wetter the weather I... ♪

22:30.016 --> 22:33.317
♪♪♪

22:33.319 --> 22:35.386
♪ don't wanna wear
without you ♪

22:35.388 --> 22:37.354
♪ I don't wanna wear you
out there ♪

22:37.390 --> 22:40.657
♪♪♪

22:40.693 --> 22:42.259
(amp squeals)
- oh, come on!

22:42.395 --> 22:44.261
- Where's your mom?
- No clue. Why?

22:44.263 --> 22:46.763
- Her presence is required
at ryan's dinnervention.

22:46.765 --> 22:48.265
Actually, as your presences.

22:48.401 --> 22:50.534
I needed asses in seats.
- What's a dinnervention?

22:50.603 --> 22:52.569
- It's me learning how
to be a loving person

22:52.571 --> 22:54.605
By feeding people and making
sure my brother doesn't...

22:54.607 --> 22:56.707
Sneak vodka into the sauce.
- Hard pass!

22:56.776 --> 22:59.543
- It's us helping your uncle
ry, okay?

22:59.545 --> 23:01.445
- Are you sure this
is for uncle ryan?

23:01.580 --> 23:03.547
- Sounds like you're workin'
an agenda.

23:03.583 --> 23:05.483
- Duh! Does it matter?

23:05.618 --> 23:07.751
Two birds brought down
by one mama bear's stone.

23:07.887 --> 23:09.587
- We're more worried
about mom right now

23:09.589 --> 23:11.388
Than you or uncle ryan.

23:11.424 --> 23:13.023
- Yeah, she's been acting
crazier than usual.

23:13.092 --> 23:15.058
- Okay, so that's great!

23:15.094 --> 23:17.027
Killing three birds
with one stone

23:17.096 --> 23:19.096
Is better than killing
two birds!

23:19.098 --> 23:21.098
- What's with you
and killing birds?

23:21.100 --> 23:22.833
- I'm going to help
your mom too, okay?

23:22.968 --> 23:25.903
But that means that you have
to be there! For your mom!

23:25.905 --> 23:27.538
And your uncle!

23:27.673 --> 23:29.940
And absolutely,
100 percent not for me,

23:30.075 --> 23:32.309
Because this isn't about me.

23:32.311 --> 23:34.611
At all.
- Right.

23:34.613 --> 23:36.546
- (sighs)
(footsteps recede)

23:37.917 --> 23:39.817
(waves lap)

23:39.819 --> 23:46.190
♪♪♪

23:47.660 --> 23:49.727
<i>Bea: Have you seen your father?</i>

23:49.862 --> 23:51.662
- Nope, not today.

23:53.533 --> 23:54.665
Everything all right?

23:54.800 --> 23:56.600
- Ah, sure.

23:56.669 --> 23:58.869
Jesus, sammy,

23:58.905 --> 24:01.137
When is anything
ever just all right?

24:01.274 --> 24:02.673
- I'll take that as a no.

24:04.177 --> 24:06.510
- How're you holding up?
- I'm a little stressed.

24:06.512 --> 24:08.546
About my interview and...

24:08.681 --> 24:11.682
I gotta figure out a plan
for my choice of field study.

24:11.817 --> 24:13.416
- You got more brains
in your big toe

24:13.453 --> 24:16.220
Than this whole outfit.
It'll sort itself out.

24:17.990 --> 24:20.224
I actually meant that fight
with ryan.

24:20.293 --> 24:21.358
- Ugh!

24:21.494 --> 24:24.094
It's like, the last thing
on my mind.

24:24.130 --> 24:26.830
My empathy tank is... On empty.

24:28.033 --> 24:31.702
- Okay. I'll offer your regrets
at this "event"

24:31.704 --> 24:33.437
That rhian's organizing.

24:33.506 --> 24:36.173
- I've been at-at all of ryan's
interventions.

24:36.175 --> 24:38.042
It-it didn't make a difference
then,

24:38.177 --> 24:39.710
It won't make a difference now.

24:39.845 --> 24:41.579
- Oh, a little cold!

24:41.714 --> 24:43.447
- Well, maybe that's how
I have to be.

24:43.582 --> 24:45.849
You know if I keep reacting
the same way

24:45.852 --> 24:48.118
And expecting different
outcomes...

24:49.522 --> 24:51.121
That's on me.

24:51.123 --> 24:53.257
- Can't fix somebody else's
bad behaviour,

24:53.326 --> 24:55.793
But you can kick yourself
in the ass.

24:55.928 --> 24:57.928
- Yeah.
- (sighs)

24:57.964 --> 24:59.797
- Maybe part of surviving
this family

24:59.799 --> 25:02.332
Is knowing when to cut bait.

25:02.368 --> 25:05.068
Maybe you found that
sweet spot. Hmm?

25:05.137 --> 25:06.904
But then again,

25:06.906 --> 25:09.340
Maybe what you're really
upset about...

25:09.342 --> 25:11.141
Isn't ryan.

25:11.210 --> 25:12.977
Hmm?

25:12.979 --> 25:14.778
(waves lap)

25:14.847 --> 25:20.751
♪♪♪

25:22.822 --> 25:26.023
Lidia: An 18-wheeler...
Of snow crabs?

25:26.092 --> 25:28.359
- Yeah, the price per pound
doubled in the last week.

25:28.361 --> 25:30.227
It's actually worth more
than crude oil.

25:30.229 --> 25:32.763
- Oh, well, I'm not
complaining. Delicious.

25:32.898 --> 25:34.765
- Okay, truck is pulling
in soon.

25:34.834 --> 25:37.434
Now you--
- the distraction. That's me!

25:37.503 --> 25:39.636
- You wave the truck down.

25:39.705 --> 25:41.438
- I've already come up
with a back story.

25:41.440 --> 25:43.774
My name's emily,
single by choice.

25:43.776 --> 25:45.909
A little, lazy day road trip.

25:45.912 --> 25:48.178
In search of love, lust,
and apparently snow crab.

25:48.314 --> 25:50.581
(chuckles)
- okay. Less is more.

25:50.583 --> 25:51.715
Just tell him your engine's
busted

25:51.751 --> 25:53.484
And your phone ran outta juice.

25:53.619 --> 25:56.053
He goes over, checks the car,
we step in... Boom.

25:56.122 --> 25:57.654
Got it. Got it!

25:58.925 --> 26:01.024
Ah! Hmm. Okay.

26:02.461 --> 26:04.261
- Okay.
- (readying exhale)

26:04.263 --> 26:07.263
- You got this.
- Yeah.

26:07.300 --> 26:09.165
- Hmm.

26:09.201 --> 26:11.267
<i> Hmm.</i>

26:11.304 --> 26:12.669
(phone buzzes)

26:15.141 --> 26:16.706
(thumb taps)

26:18.110 --> 26:20.811
(phone rings)

26:20.813 --> 26:23.213
- Oh! So good to know
I can rely on you

26:23.282 --> 26:25.816
As my emergency contact.
- What's going on?

26:25.818 --> 26:27.384
Are you okay?
- I'm grand.

26:27.453 --> 26:28.852
Our brother,
on the other hand,

26:28.854 --> 26:30.821
Has some serious issues
to work out,

26:30.823 --> 26:33.423
So dinnervention, 18h00.
Attendance mandatory.

26:33.492 --> 26:35.291
Oh! Bring that salad with
the feta and the strawberries.

26:35.328 --> 26:37.194
- I can't make the salad.
Sorry.

26:37.263 --> 26:39.696
- Then throw some iceberg
and croutons into a bowl.

26:40.933 --> 26:42.833
<i> - I'm kinda tied up</i>
<i> with something.</i>

26:42.902 --> 26:45.969
(hand pounds on knife)
- look, lidz,

26:45.972 --> 26:48.572
<i>I know that you've been through</i>
<i> the wringer lately,</i>

26:48.707 --> 26:51.107
And I-I wanna be here for you.

26:51.243 --> 26:52.909
- Wow, rhian, did your aneurysm
finally pop?

26:52.945 --> 26:55.445
<i> - I simply care</i>
<i> about this family!</i>

26:55.481 --> 26:57.381
Maybe you've forgotten
what that means?

26:57.516 --> 26:59.315
- I do lots for this family.

26:59.352 --> 27:01.251
Like, a dangerous,
above and beyond, amount.

27:01.253 --> 27:02.719
- Then get your ass home!

27:02.755 --> 27:05.622
- Oh, I'll get there
as soon as I can. I promise.

27:05.625 --> 27:07.424
<i> - Where are you?</i>

27:07.460 --> 27:09.325
(truck rumbles)

27:10.463 --> 27:12.062
Lidia? (gasps)
(dial tone)

27:13.366 --> 27:15.065
She better have lost service.
(phone clatters)

27:16.369 --> 27:19.069
(truck rumbles)
- oh, uh, right here!

27:19.105 --> 27:20.804
Oh, hi!

27:20.806 --> 27:23.273
Stop! Stop, stop!

27:23.275 --> 27:25.375
(airbrakes hiss)

27:25.444 --> 27:27.944
(rumbles to a stop,
door opens, shuts)

27:30.182 --> 27:32.949
Oh, my gosh!
Thank you so much for stopping!

27:33.019 --> 27:35.351
My car broke down
and my phone is dead.

27:35.388 --> 27:36.887
I've been waiting for hours.
- Lift?

27:36.889 --> 27:39.322
- Uh, do you actually mind
taking a look?

27:39.392 --> 27:40.791
This has happened before.

27:40.926 --> 27:42.559
Sometimes you just need
to jiggle something.

27:42.695 --> 27:44.027
- I got tools.
Just pop the hood.

27:44.030 --> 27:46.296
- Oh, b-b-but before
you do that,

27:47.700 --> 27:49.099
Do you know this area well?

27:49.234 --> 27:51.568
Uh, I'm from new york. Well,
I'm technically from brooklyn,

27:51.570 --> 27:52.969
Which if we're being honest,
is more new york

27:53.005 --> 27:55.105
Than manhattan, these days,
amirite?

27:55.141 --> 27:57.440
(lidia's phone rings)
- you said your phone's dead?

27:57.442 --> 27:59.676
- It is.
Do you hear a phone?

28:01.681 --> 28:03.346
- Still ringing.
- Uh...

28:03.416 --> 28:05.182
- You okay, miss?
(thud blows)

28:05.184 --> 28:06.850
- Oh no! Oh, my god!
(crashes to ground)

28:06.852 --> 28:08.785
- My god! Did you have
to hit him so hard?

28:08.854 --> 28:10.820
- Yep.
- Is he bleeding?

28:10.856 --> 28:12.789
Oh, he's so nice.
He called me "miss".

28:12.858 --> 28:14.658
Should we get him some ice?

28:14.793 --> 28:18.061
Body rasps heavily on gravel)
lidia: Oh!

28:18.197 --> 28:20.464
(truck rumbles away)

28:20.533 --> 28:26.669
♪♪♪

28:27.673 --> 28:29.339
(remorseful exhale)

28:35.047 --> 28:38.248
♪♪♪

28:38.383 --> 28:39.849
(content exhale)

28:39.885 --> 28:43.419
♪ I'm sayin' no
while I'm taking it ♪

28:45.758 --> 28:47.958
- Artisan meatballs, sis.
God's greatest hits.

28:48.093 --> 28:50.227
Where is everyone?
- They'll be here.

28:50.229 --> 28:52.162
You know lidia, her picture's
in the dictionary

28:52.198 --> 28:53.897
Next to "I brought
the fanciest side".

28:53.899 --> 28:55.565
- Maybe we should start.

28:55.601 --> 28:57.101
You know, word of my emotional
awakening will spread

28:57.236 --> 28:58.969
Across the campground
and sammy and crystal

28:58.971 --> 29:00.504
Will be here in time
for cupcakes.

29:00.639 --> 29:04.240
♪♪♪

29:04.276 --> 29:06.043
- I can do this.
- Hey, ken!

29:06.045 --> 29:07.511
- Hey, dad.

29:07.646 --> 29:09.313
Leave it to rhian to make
this a potluck.

29:09.315 --> 29:11.047
What do you bring
to a dinnervention?

29:11.049 --> 29:12.882
- Ah, ketchup chips suit me
just fine.

29:12.918 --> 29:15.619
Not sure about the cocktail
onions.

29:15.754 --> 29:17.521
(nora's phone rings)

29:17.590 --> 29:19.256
♪ to whither away

29:19.325 --> 29:21.058
<i> - What?</i>
<i> Andres: Nora,</i>

29:21.060 --> 29:23.059
<i>It's andres from soundmaus la</i>
<i> again.</i>

29:23.061 --> 29:24.995
<i> I've been trying to get</i>
<i> in contact with you</i>

29:24.997 --> 29:26.930
<i> About your show.</i>
<i> It's fire.</i>

29:26.932 --> 29:28.999
<i> We'd love to be a part</i>
<i> of branding your unique--</i>

29:29.068 --> 29:32.269
- It's a spam call.
Where the hell is lidia?

29:32.404 --> 29:34.037
- Ah, she's probably just late.

29:34.073 --> 29:36.673
However, if she is smart,
avoiding this spectacle.

29:36.675 --> 29:38.342
- Make way, make way.

29:38.477 --> 29:40.277
Please be advised that we
are in a holding pattern

29:40.279 --> 29:42.245
Until the rest
of the guests arrive.

29:42.281 --> 29:43.980
(notepad plops on table)

29:43.982 --> 29:46.783
♪ please forgive me
this insanity ♪

29:49.155 --> 29:52.488
- I can do the silent
treatment baloney too, old man.

29:53.592 --> 29:55.258
But I'm not going to.

29:55.327 --> 29:57.094
Because I'm not a child.

29:57.229 --> 29:59.229
You're overreacting.
It was a scene.

29:59.364 --> 30:02.432
It's... Theatre.
- Apparently, theatre is truth.

30:02.434 --> 30:04.968
And it sure looked real to me.

30:05.004 --> 30:07.570
♪♪♪

30:07.572 --> 30:10.240
- Who's that?
- Our director.

30:10.276 --> 30:12.809
- Your director.
- He looks fun.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.845
- You invited him?

30:14.847 --> 30:16.779
- I mentioned our son's
issues to him.

30:16.816 --> 30:19.283
And he volunteered
to come help the family

30:19.285 --> 30:21.518
Access our emotions.
(smitten chuckle)

30:21.653 --> 30:24.588
♪♪♪

30:24.657 --> 30:26.390
(machine whirs)

30:29.195 --> 30:31.160
(machine beeps)

30:33.165 --> 30:35.531
Maybe we should call someone.
- About?

30:35.568 --> 30:37.467
- Uh, the unsuspecting trucker

30:37.469 --> 30:38.902
We left on the side
of the road?

30:39.037 --> 30:41.037
- He'll be fine.
- He could be concussed.

30:41.039 --> 30:42.939
His brain could be swelling.
He could be dead.

30:43.074 --> 30:45.209
- He's a long-haul trucker.
They gotta call in to dispatch

30:45.344 --> 30:47.878
Every hour, on the hour.
When he doesn't,

30:47.880 --> 30:50.080
They'll just locate the gps
on his truck.

30:50.082 --> 30:51.915
- Yeah, which they'll find
abandoned.

30:52.050 --> 30:54.384
- So, they'll backtrack
his route and find him.

30:54.420 --> 30:56.486
Lidia, it's okay.

30:56.555 --> 30:58.322
I got this.

30:58.324 --> 31:00.223
Now... (claps hands)

31:00.259 --> 31:02.159
How 'bout that dinner?

31:02.294 --> 31:06.429
♪♪♪

31:06.498 --> 31:08.164
Davide: The whole community
is rooting

31:08.200 --> 31:10.667
For your recovery, ryan.
- Took a poll, did'ja?

31:10.736 --> 31:12.836
- Like many artists,
I too have...

31:12.838 --> 31:15.305
Tangoed with addiction.

31:15.440 --> 31:17.174
- Fascinating.
(nora's phone chimes)

31:23.215 --> 31:25.315
(low hum of chatter)

31:25.351 --> 31:27.250
Ryan: Can't keep waiting for
the rest of them, rhian.

31:27.286 --> 31:29.252
Maybe I should make amends
with the family that are here.

31:29.254 --> 31:30.687
- Ryan--
- hey, bruce!

31:30.756 --> 31:32.789
- Hi, bruce.
- Thanks for coming, man.

31:32.858 --> 31:34.391
- Wouldn't missed it.
Proud of you, kid.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.192
And I was told
there'd be meatballs.

31:36.262 --> 31:38.128
- Mm-hmm.
- Right?

31:38.197 --> 31:39.862
(ryan clears his throat)

31:39.899 --> 31:42.265
Once upon a time,
in a galaxy...

31:42.301 --> 31:44.267
Well, this galaxy, actually,

31:44.403 --> 31:47.471
There was a boy.
His name was ryan.

31:47.606 --> 31:50.073
And even though he misspelt
his name with an "I"

31:50.109 --> 31:53.343
Until the third grade,
he could say it perfectly.

31:53.379 --> 31:55.878
Loud and proud.
And I say it now.

31:57.149 --> 31:59.082
"my name is ryan."

31:59.217 --> 32:00.984
Welcome to my dinnervention.

32:01.119 --> 32:02.785
Bea: Nice.

32:03.889 --> 32:05.822
Oscar: Slather,
double letter on the h,

32:05.891 --> 32:07.891
Triple word score.
37 points!

32:07.893 --> 32:10.160
Eat it, rashaad97,
you stupid fu--

32:10.229 --> 32:11.695
(phone rings)

32:11.764 --> 32:13.029
(chair rattles)

32:14.300 --> 32:16.633
You've reached foxton pd.
This is oscar finley-cullen.

32:16.768 --> 32:18.201
How may I be of service?

32:19.304 --> 32:20.837
Hijacking?

32:20.839 --> 32:22.172
Snow crabs?

32:24.710 --> 32:26.042
(stammers)
help is on the way.

32:26.111 --> 32:28.044
(receiver clunks)

32:29.781 --> 32:32.115
<i> Ryan: And on that day,</i>
<i> this day,</i>

32:32.117 --> 32:34.050
<i> Young ryan stopped being</i>
<i> so young.</i>

32:34.119 --> 32:36.519
Not old exactly,
but you know,

32:36.588 --> 32:38.188
38's the new 16, right, sis?
(chuckles)

32:40.759 --> 32:43.059
Planet earth voyaged
around the sun

32:44.262 --> 32:46.730
Until ryan decided
to clean up his act.

32:46.799 --> 32:48.732
And become a man.
- Nice.

32:50.002 --> 32:51.234
(clapping)
okay.

32:52.705 --> 32:54.338
- That was very brave.

32:54.473 --> 32:56.006
We all love you.

32:56.008 --> 32:58.775
I-I'd just like to add--
davide: Bravo. (claps)

32:58.910 --> 33:01.378
What courage.
What candor.

33:01.447 --> 33:03.613
A confessional tour de force.
Revelatory--

33:03.749 --> 33:05.749
- Cram it, prince charles.

33:05.818 --> 33:07.184
Not your place.

33:07.319 --> 33:09.152
- Ah, perhaps it's not
my place.

33:09.154 --> 33:11.021
Or yours.

33:11.023 --> 33:13.490
But it is ryan's place.

33:13.492 --> 33:15.525
Misguided, maladjusted,

33:15.527 --> 33:17.227
Unsupported ryan.

33:17.296 --> 33:19.629
Just a guess.
- You're blaming us?

33:19.698 --> 33:21.297
- Blame is rooted in fear.

33:22.468 --> 33:24.034
Embrace love, ken.

33:24.169 --> 33:25.701
All the answers you need
are right there

33:25.738 --> 33:27.671
In ryan's story.

33:27.673 --> 33:29.239
What do you think, ryan?

33:29.374 --> 33:32.509
What is at the heart
of your addiction?

33:32.511 --> 33:34.244
- That's a toughie, davide.

33:34.246 --> 33:36.646
I like to drink.
Makes me feel better.

33:36.682 --> 33:39.116
But then it makes me
feel worse.

33:39.251 --> 33:41.851
- Yes! Yes, keep going.
This is good.

33:41.920 --> 33:43.887
Dig deeper. Why?

33:44.022 --> 33:45.655
Why does it make you
feel worse?

33:45.691 --> 33:48.291
- Enough of this bull!
- Let him talk.

33:48.360 --> 33:51.194
He's an artist.
Maybe he has some insights.

33:51.196 --> 33:53.663
- Insight? Artist?

33:53.665 --> 33:56.933
The man played a chicken
in a tv commercial in 2001!

33:56.935 --> 33:59.102
- (chuckling)
- oh yeah, I googled ya, pal.

33:59.237 --> 34:00.937
- Dad knows google?

34:00.939 --> 34:03.005
- It was a rooster,
and it was a national campaign.

34:03.042 --> 34:04.541
- Your accent?

34:04.610 --> 34:07.243
You're from oshawa!
Ha, ha, ha!

34:07.279 --> 34:09.512
- I spent some time
treading the boards

34:09.581 --> 34:11.214
In london's west end.

34:11.349 --> 34:13.382
- This is not part
of the healing process.

34:13.419 --> 34:14.984
- Think back, ryan.

34:15.054 --> 34:16.653
Read between the lines
of your story.

34:16.788 --> 34:18.754
What is your subtext?

34:18.756 --> 34:21.291
What trauma did you suffer?

34:21.293 --> 34:23.259
- That trauma is you, pal!

34:23.261 --> 34:25.228
- I wanna know what he writes
in the dirty black book.

34:25.230 --> 34:27.097
- Okay, everyone, enough.

34:27.099 --> 34:29.633
- This is not about
your baggage, okay?!

34:29.768 --> 34:31.535
Or your obviously fake accent.

34:31.537 --> 34:33.670
This is about ryan.

34:33.805 --> 34:35.205
Ryan.

34:35.340 --> 34:38.775
And my deep, maternal,
nourishing well.

34:38.910 --> 34:40.776
- No one's here to judge,
rhian.

34:40.813 --> 34:42.778
Or blame, rhian.

34:42.815 --> 34:45.214
We only seek the truth.

34:49.588 --> 34:51.988
(meatball thumps, splatters)
all: Oh!

34:52.124 --> 34:53.723
(ken laughs)

34:53.725 --> 34:55.358
- That is your truth.

34:55.494 --> 34:57.193
I am here to witness it.

34:58.263 --> 35:00.197
And to play a part
in your shame.

35:01.300 --> 35:04.033
(meatball splatters)
(all gasp)

35:05.804 --> 35:07.570
- Bring it... Mime!

35:08.607 --> 35:10.206
(van rumbles slowly)

35:12.010 --> 35:13.209
(brakes squeak)

35:15.647 --> 35:17.280
(cuts engine)

35:17.282 --> 35:19.015
Crystal: Sammy!

35:19.151 --> 35:20.817
(door creaks open)

35:20.952 --> 35:22.485
Are you ready to go?

35:22.488 --> 35:24.954
'cause you are walking in the
wrong direction from the city.

35:25.023 --> 35:26.989
Ooh, brownies!
(gasps)

35:28.059 --> 35:30.026
You're going to ryan's
dinnervention.

35:30.161 --> 35:31.761
- (emotional exhale)
I know I...

35:31.897 --> 35:34.097
I don't need to drive
in tonight

35:34.099 --> 35:36.032
For an interview tomorrow.
I-I can--

35:36.034 --> 35:38.535
- Can what? Sammy, what?

35:38.670 --> 35:40.604
You're gonna make the same
mistake

35:40.606 --> 35:42.705
That you've made and
that I've made before,

35:42.774 --> 35:45.175
And then, it's somehow
gonna be different?

35:45.177 --> 35:47.243
Like, you know what
that is, right?

35:47.312 --> 35:50.513
- A brother tryin' to do
the right thing?

35:50.516 --> 35:52.515
I dunno, a brother who...

35:52.518 --> 35:54.317
May be upset about something
else entirely.

35:54.319 --> 35:56.386
Crystal, you know,
it's not ryan's fault

35:56.388 --> 35:58.121
That we hit a dead end
looking for my bio mom.

35:58.190 --> 35:59.890
- No. But...

36:00.025 --> 36:02.858
That insanity... Probably is.

36:02.895 --> 36:05.729
♪ la, la, la, la, la, la,
la, la, la, la ♪

36:05.864 --> 36:08.798
♪ la, la, la, la, la, la,
la, la, la, la ♪

36:08.933 --> 36:12.468
♪ la, la, la, la, la, la,
la, la, la, la, la, la ♪

36:15.340 --> 36:18.408
♪ now that I've lost
everything to you ♪

36:18.543 --> 36:21.744
♪ you say you wanna
start something new ♪

36:21.813 --> 36:25.748
♪ and it's breakin' my heart
you're leavin' ♪

36:25.817 --> 36:27.617
♪ baby, I'm grievin'

36:27.686 --> 36:29.686
♪but if you wanna leave,
take good care ♪

36:29.755 --> 36:31.855
- Is that the life you want?

36:31.857 --> 36:34.624
♪ I hope you have a lot
of nice things to wear ♪

36:34.660 --> 36:38.428
♪ but then a lot of nice
things turn bad out there ♪

36:39.932 --> 36:43.033
- Come on. We can eat
the brownies on the way.

36:43.035 --> 36:46.369
♪ ooh, baby, baby,
it's a wild world ♪

36:47.573 --> 36:50.073
- Sammy!
Crystal, where you goin'?

36:50.208 --> 36:52.108
♪ it's hard to get by
just upon a smile ♪

36:54.079 --> 36:55.545
There are cupcakes!

36:55.614 --> 36:58.581
♪ oh, baby, baby,
it's a wild world ♪

37:01.086 --> 37:04.320
♪ and I'll always remember
you like a child, girl ♪

37:08.860 --> 37:10.626
(loud cheering, rock music)

37:10.662 --> 37:17.600
♪♪♪

37:17.669 --> 37:24.674
♪♪♪

37:24.676 --> 37:32.349
♪♪♪

37:32.351 --> 37:34.017
- Hmm.

37:34.152 --> 37:35.551
Thanks.

37:35.687 --> 37:37.654
- Behold. The club.

37:39.558 --> 37:42.091
- Yeah, they are...

37:42.127 --> 37:44.527
Quite something.
- (chuckles)

37:44.529 --> 37:46.096
You...

37:46.098 --> 37:47.930
You were great today.

37:47.966 --> 37:50.633
Most people woulda run
at the first sign of trouble.

37:50.702 --> 37:52.368
But not you.
Which got me thinkin'.

37:53.438 --> 37:55.338
- Sounds serious.
- Could be.

37:55.407 --> 37:57.373
- You're the first woman
that I've ever been with

37:57.409 --> 38:00.110
That I... I could uh...

38:00.245 --> 38:01.811
See a future with.

38:01.813 --> 38:04.114
Together.

38:04.116 --> 38:05.648
- Together, like...

38:05.651 --> 38:07.350
Together, together?

38:07.485 --> 38:10.052
- Like, I could get a tattoo
of your name, together.

38:10.088 --> 38:12.922
- (nervous chuckle)
- I see a future for us.

38:12.958 --> 38:15.058
In life, in-in love,

38:15.127 --> 38:16.659
In... In business.

38:18.096 --> 38:20.130
- My business.
- Your, your family business.

38:20.265 --> 38:21.498
And mine.

38:21.633 --> 38:23.299
- Whew.

38:23.302 --> 38:24.668
- The marauders
and the moonshine.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.269
A-a mutually beneficial
relationship.

38:27.306 --> 38:28.338
It's the,
it's the perfect place...

38:29.541 --> 38:32.675
To lay down roots.
We'd be, we'd be partners.

38:32.678 --> 38:34.277
In every way.

38:35.614 --> 38:37.280
- Partners.

38:37.282 --> 38:38.681
- I invest...

38:38.750 --> 38:41.283
And the-the club becomes
legal shareholders.

38:41.320 --> 38:43.252
- The moonshine is far
from legal.

38:43.322 --> 38:44.754
I mean... We don't even
have a deed.

38:44.889 --> 38:47.157
- Ha, ha, I got a guy
can make that happen.

38:47.159 --> 38:50.093
Whatever we need to make
the moonshine legit.

38:51.997 --> 38:53.496
What you want.

38:54.800 --> 38:56.899
What you need.

38:56.935 --> 38:58.768
I can give.

38:58.804 --> 39:05.775
♪♪♪

39:05.811 --> 39:10.380
♪♪♪

39:13.151 --> 39:14.417
(hinges creak)

39:15.854 --> 39:18.121
(waves lap)

39:18.190 --> 39:20.590
(distant playful shouting)

39:22.861 --> 39:25.027
(waves lap)

39:30.335 --> 39:31.801
Nora: God!
(spoon rasps)

39:31.870 --> 39:33.570
Gross.
(footsteps thud)

39:34.673 --> 39:36.505
You hear from your mom yet?

39:36.541 --> 39:38.441
- No, her phone's dead.

39:38.576 --> 39:40.910
- This just so isn't like her.

39:40.979 --> 39:43.413
- Yeah, she's been
a little loopy lately.

39:43.548 --> 39:45.215
- Define loopy.

39:45.350 --> 39:46.749
- We caught her talking
to herself,

39:46.818 --> 39:48.484
Like full-on conversation.

39:48.520 --> 39:50.352
Like she was talking
to the air.

39:50.389 --> 39:52.288
- Debating the air, really.

39:52.324 --> 39:54.791
Is 40 too young for dementia?
- Yeah.

39:54.860 --> 39:56.759
Yeah, it is.

39:56.762 --> 39:58.661
(hand taps lovingly)

39:58.730 --> 40:00.163
(footsteps recede)

40:00.232 --> 40:02.164
- Can't believe
we're not composting.

40:02.200 --> 40:04.434
What is this, the 80s?
- Okay, I am super worried.

40:04.569 --> 40:07.770
- I appreciate your concern
for me.

40:07.839 --> 40:11.007
- No, dumb shit, lidia.
I'm worried about our sister.

40:11.009 --> 40:12.742
- Oh.
- What about your sister?

40:12.877 --> 40:15.578
- She's been boning that biker
and now she's gone awol.

40:15.580 --> 40:18.514
- Huh, I'm actually pretty
worried about her myself.

40:19.584 --> 40:21.851
Did that sound natural?
That felt natural.

40:21.853 --> 40:23.519
- No offence, girls,

40:23.655 --> 40:26.189
But of the three of you,
my money is on blondie...

40:26.191 --> 40:28.658
From new york.
- Brooklyn, actually.

40:28.793 --> 40:30.527
So...

40:30.662 --> 40:32.862
Funny story.

40:32.997 --> 40:36.666
♪♪♪

40:36.801 --> 40:38.601
(van rumbles)

40:41.640 --> 40:43.539
(door clunks closed)

40:43.575 --> 40:46.376
(footsteps crunch)

40:46.378 --> 40:48.410
Lidia: Hi! What're you
doing here? Wait, I mean,

40:48.447 --> 40:51.214
Should a leblanc be cross
pollinating with marauders?

40:51.216 --> 40:54.150
- Unfortunately, bees have
nothing to do with this.

40:54.152 --> 40:56.819
I just got a call from my mom
in prison,

40:56.822 --> 40:59.421
And there is something
that I think you should know.

41:00.959 --> 41:02.791
(indistinct whispers)

41:06.431 --> 41:08.031
Lidia: Okay.

41:12.337 --> 41:14.370
(van door closes,
engine starts)

41:15.740 --> 41:17.573
(van rumbles away)
gale: Who was that?

41:17.709 --> 41:21.443
- Uh...
My-my brother's girlfriend.

41:21.480 --> 41:23.312
Ex-girlfriend.
Hard to keep track.

41:25.116 --> 41:26.582
- There a problem?

41:26.718 --> 41:28.918
- The 18-wheeler we boosted...

41:29.053 --> 41:30.986
Was a leblanc truck.

41:32.290 --> 41:33.923
- That is a problem.
- I know.

41:33.959 --> 41:35.925
I mean, I'm new to the crime
thing, but crystal says

41:35.961 --> 41:38.394
We may have unintentionally
started a turf war.

41:38.530 --> 41:41.063
- Look you, just droppin'
"boosted" and "turf war"

41:41.099 --> 41:42.598
Like a pro. (chuckles)

41:44.836 --> 41:48.271
- Wait, you knew
it was a leblanc truck?

41:48.340 --> 41:51.274
- The business I had in uh,
new brunswick.

41:51.343 --> 41:53.209
Chapter's looking to expand

41:53.344 --> 41:55.778
And with the leblanc's
matriarch in prison,

41:55.780 --> 41:57.647
Foxton's up for grabs.

41:57.649 --> 41:59.749
- Was that not information
you might have shared with me

41:59.818 --> 42:01.584
Before dragging me into this?

42:01.653 --> 42:04.086
- I didn't drag you
into anything. You volunteered.

42:04.088 --> 42:07.156
(shocked exhale)
- gale... Oh, my god.

42:08.826 --> 42:10.893
I just need to pay
my family's tax bill.

42:10.896 --> 42:13.162
- I know, I know,
this is a lot to process.

42:13.198 --> 42:14.764
- Yeah.

42:14.833 --> 42:16.299
So, what now?

42:16.434 --> 42:19.369
- Well, these things don't
usually end in hugs.

42:19.371 --> 42:21.237
There will be some retaliation.
- (worried exhale)

42:21.372 --> 42:23.472
- But things... Things
will calm down. Eventually.

42:24.709 --> 42:26.976
- Shit. My family's having
a dinner thing. I'm late.

42:27.012 --> 42:29.312
I gotta go.
- Of course.

42:31.049 --> 42:32.615
Don't worry.

42:32.750 --> 42:34.584
As long as you're in the club,

42:34.719 --> 42:37.120
You will be protected.

42:37.255 --> 42:43.993
♪♪♪

42:44.128 --> 42:45.661
(hollering, party chatter)

42:45.697 --> 42:49.064
♪♪♪

42:49.100 --> 42:50.866
- (sighs heavily)

42:50.902 --> 42:53.402
(footsteps crunch)

42:56.942 --> 42:58.741
(locusts chirping)

42:58.876 --> 43:01.077
- Oh, god!

43:01.212 --> 43:03.145
(chirping intensifies)

43:03.181 --> 43:04.747
Hello?
(leaves rustling)

43:04.783 --> 43:06.883
Who's there?

43:06.885 --> 43:08.451
(gasps)

43:08.453 --> 43:10.420
- (laughs)

43:10.422 --> 43:12.288
(bag rustles)
lidia: Ah!

43:15.460 --> 43:22.365
♪♪♪

43:22.500 --> 43:29.539
♪♪♪

43:29.541 --> 43:35.444
♪♪♪

43:35.480 --> 43:42.986
♪♪♪
